  Instrument Overview
  ===================
    The McDonald P45a Two-Channel Photometer has an uncooled RCA 8850
    photomultiplier as its primary channel, with an uncooled RCA 4516
    photomultiplier as its secondary channel.  The instrument is described in
    Binzel and Mulholland (1983).
 
    Binzel, R.P. and J.D. Mulholland, Photometry of Pluto during the 1982
    opposition, Astron. J. 88, 222-225, 1983.

